Lets consider a bank

it acts like as an intermediary between multiple people in supporting financial transactions in exchange the bank will charge some fee(commition). yet the transactions sometimes takes long time to complete and are unavailable during weekends.on top of it the banks have the central authority on the behavior its members and there is a possibility of double spending.sometimes banks are vulnerable to cyber attacks.


in 2009 Satoshi Nakamoto published Bitcoin white paper and introduced bitcoin a peer to peer electronic system to the world which solves the many of the central systems fail to address as bitcoin is built on blockchain technology which has components such as decentralised architecture,distributed ledger,consensus algorithm,cryptographic algorithm and incentives .

so here there will be No intermediaries,No holidays,No double spending, low transaction fees and Highly secured.

 
